benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from account

covered: DELETE Valid Deletion: TC01–TC04 cover standard removal flows (no param, specific fields, all fields) with 204 responses and GET verification.
DELETE Non-Existent Resource: TC06 demonstrates idempotent deletion for non-existent accounts (204).
DELETE Concurrency: TC16 tests 100 concurrent DELETE calls; 204 statuses and acceptable response times.
Authorization: TC07 (missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header) and TC10 (unauthorized), cover auth failure paths.
Error Handling: TC11 (backend service unavailable -> 500) and TC12 (network timeout -> 504).
Input Validation: TC05 validates accountId format; TC08 and TC20 validate customField IDs (UUID and XSS), returning 400.
Query Parameters: TC09 (extra unsupported param) and TC13 (large number of customField IDs) and TC14 (duplicate IDs) test parameter handling and idempotency.
Regression/Idempotency: TC15 ensures second DELETE on same field returns 204 with no body.
Integration/Data Consistency: TC17 ensures downstream references reflect deletion.
State Variation: TC18 removes from partially populated accounts without affecting existing fields.
Security: TC19 (SQL injection in accountId) and TC20 (XSS in customField) produce 400 with error messages.
Optional Headers: TC03 validates optional headers (X-Killbill-Reason, X-Killbill-Comment) are accepted and logged.
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit test ensuring logical vs physical deletion semantics (soft delete) is covered.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling / burst scenarios.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating ETag / Cache-Control headers on DELETE or subsequent GETs.
Pagination on GET results: Not tested within this suite (GET verifications exist but not paginated).
Observability/Logging: No tests verifying logs or traces for DELETE operations.
recommendations: Add dedicated soft-delete semantics test (logical vs physical removal).
Add rate-limiting tests (throttling, burst, and quota checks).
Add caching headers validation (ETag/Cache-Control) on GET after deletions.
Add pagination tests for GET listing of custom fields when large datasets are present.
Add observability tests validating logs/traces for delete operations.
